Uses of Package
jsx.http.event

Packages that use jsx.http.event
jsx.http.event Event objects and their handlers for HTTP requests. 
jsx.http.rpc Facilitates mechanism for RPC based on HTTP serialization. 
 

Classes in jsx.http.event used by jsx.http.event
HTTPAborted
          A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the state of its HTTP transmission has been aborted.
HTTPLoaded
          A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the state of its HTTP transmission has been completed.
HTTPOpen
          A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the session of its HTTP transmission has just been opened.
HTTPReceiving
          A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when it has just started to be receiving HTTP data.
HTTPSent
          A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when it has just sent a request for receiving data to an opened HTTP session.
HTTPState
          An abstract type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object to notify a state of HTTP transmission.
OnHTTPAborted
          Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPAborted type.
OnHTTPLoaded
          Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPLoaded type.
OnHTTPOpen
          Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPOpen type.
OnHTTPReceiving
          Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPReceiving type.
OnHTTPSent
          Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPSent type.
 

Classes in jsx.http.event used by jsx.http.rpc
HTTPLoaded
          A type of high level events that may be fired from a Ajax object when the state of its HTTP transmission has been completed.

          Declares an interface for high level event listeners that handle events of the HTTPLoaded type.
